Talents are the key to rural revitalization.
Where to find talents?
Outstanding returning migrant workers are an indispensable force.
Issued by Xinhua News Agency Written by Shang Haichun
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26. Title: Turn outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization
Zhang Xiong, 34, lives in Guoyuan Village, Meishan City, Sichuan Province. In 2010, he quit his job in Beijing with a monthly salary of tens of thousands and returned to his hometown to start a business.
After several years of hard work, the annual income of the grape-growing family farm he manages now exceeds one million yuan, and he has become a well-known leader in getting rich. He has also been selected into the village’s “two committees” team.
In recent years, inspired by a series of policies to support agriculture and benefit agriculture, such as national poverty alleviation and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return to their hometowns to start their own businesses, which has activated a pool of spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, a province with a large population in western my country and a large labor exporting province, has implemented the “Excellent Migrant Workers Recruitment Training Project” in accordance with the situation. In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries were generated from the outstanding migrant workers to cultivate village reserve forces. There are 61,000 members and more than 20,000 party members have been recruited to provide a strong guarantee for winning the fight against poverty and implementing the strategy of rural revitalization.
Whether a well-off society or not a well-off society depends on the villagers.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged laborers in rural my country have gone out to work to increase their income.
However, objectively, it also led to the emergence of “hollowing” to varying degrees in rural areas, especially the weakening of rural grassroots organizations. The village party branch secretaries and party members all showed the characteristics of “one old and one low”, that is, aging, low education, and the village party The team leader is not strong, and the problem of non-compliance is prominent.
If rural talents and other factors have been flowing to the cities one-way, and the rural areas have been in a state of “blood loss” and “anemia” for a long time, revitalization is empty talk.
To attract back those migrant workers who are capable, conscious, and aspiring to serve their hometowns, and guide them to return to their hometowns to start businesses and become wealthy leaders. From among them, they can become party members and rural cadres and enrich the grassroots cadre team. This is to solve the problem of rural party members. A permanent solution that is not in contact with the grassroots party organizations.
Excellent migrant workers can be attracted back, but they must be retained and done well.
In recent years, Sichuan has begun to pay close attention to the party building of migrant workers. On the basis of strict selection criteria, it has established systems and mechanisms for outstanding migrant workers’ directional referral, service guarantee, training and promotion, and selection and use, so that they can improve their abilities and work. There is a guarantee of security, hope in life, truly taking root in the countryside, and a sense of accomplishment in starting a business.
This year is the final year of the decisive battle against poverty. To do a good job of linking poverty alleviation with rural revitalization, talents are the key factor.
Party committees and governments at all levels must attach great importance to the group of outstanding migrant workers who have returned to their hometowns, and through comprehensive measures, they will be transformed into a team and a new force that can be retained, fight, and cannot be taken away, so as to provide support for poverty alleviation and development in rural areas Strong organizational guarantee and talent support.
