Francis Semwenza, a current affairs commentator in Tanzania, said that China’s above decision is a legitimate and necessary response to the provocation of the United States.
If Sino-US relations are to return to normal, the US should take the initiative to improve relations with China and stop interfering in China’s internal affairs.
The United States should focus on how to achieve economic and political win-win with China, and how to benefit the two peoples and the entire international community.
Ali Youssef, executive director of the Arab-Chinese Youyi Association Federation based in Sudan, said that the countermeasures China was forced to take were a legitimate and necessary response to the unreasonable actions of the United States, and conformed to the basic norms of international law and international relations, as well as diplomacy. Convention.
Previously, the US request to close the Chinese Consulate General in Houston seriously violated international law and the basic norms of international relations.
It is hoped that the US will revoke the previous relevant decisions and create necessary conditions for the return of bilateral relations to normal.
Singapore’s “Lianhe Zaobao” published an editorial saying that the greater strategic intention of the United States is to contain China and prevent China from continuing to rise.
In the face of the United States’ pressing steadily, although China is very unwilling to see Sino-US relations continue to deteriorate, it has to take countermeasures.
