Four departments launch a new round of App governance to protect personal information security-Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, July 25 (Reporters Yu Junjie and Chen Aiping) Reporters learned from the Cyberspace Administration of China on the 25th that the 2020 App illegal collection and use of personal information governance work has been officially launched recently, focusing on cracking down on private uploading of personal information in the App background, etc. The masses reported strong problems.
It is reported that this round of App governance was carried out by the four departments of the State Cyberspace Administration of China, the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology, the Ministry of Public Security, and the State Administration for Market Regulation.
According to reports, the special governance working group composed of four departments received more than 12,000 effective reports from netizens last year, conducted inspections on more than 2,300 apps, and adopted public exposure and agreement on 260 apps with large-scale users and prominent problems. Punishment measures such as talks and removals.
According to the relevant person in charge of the National Cyberspace Administration of China, the current number of apps has exceeded 5 million, and the problem of illegal collection and use of personal information has not been fundamentally resolved.
In 2020, the governance work will be further strengthened. Based on App verification, the governance scope will be further expanded to SDK (software development kit) and small programs.
It is reported that the working group will conduct special research and in-depth inspections on issues such as the irregular collection and use of personal biometric information and the abuse of sensitive permissions by apps, with a focus on background permission abuses such as recording and photographing.
Based on the circumstances of the problem and the severity of the consequences, the working group will impose penalties such as interviews, warnings, removals, and fines in accordance with laws and regulations to form an effective deterrent to violations of laws and regulations.
It is understood that the working group plans to formulate and publish App Store Commentary and Management Guidelines for the Collection and Use of Personal Information of Apps, to guide and urge app stores to do a good job of reviewing apps before they go live, and to strictly control entry points.
In addition, the working group will also release free technical tools to guide small and medium-sized enterprises to conduct self-test assessments and improve the legal compliance of their personal information collection and use activities.
