Chongqing Wulong landslide forms barrier lake, local emergency transfers more than 500 people-Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Chongqing, July 26 (Reporters Zhou Wenchong, Ke Gaoyang) A reporter learned from the Wulong District Government of Chongqing City on the 26th that heavy rains caused landslides in the area and formed a barrier lake, and more than 500 people were urgently transferred.
Affected by continuous rainfall, since July 22, the soil at the rear edge of the Zhongbao landslide in the Zhongtai Group, Liujing Village, Didi Township, Wulong District, has cracked and a large area of ​​sliding deformation has occurred, and the landslide has fallen into the Wujiang tributary along the Canghe River.
On the 25th, there was a strong rainfall in the local area, and the landslide further expanded, causing the village road to be interrupted and completely blocked along the Cang River, forming a dammed lake with a water level of 13 meters in front of the dam and a storage capacity of about 420,000 cubic meters.
According to on-site investigation and monitoring, the landslide has a volume of about 1.3 million cubic meters and is still in an unstable state with sporadic rockfalls. The barrier lake has overflowed the dam, and there is a risk of dike failure, posing a threat to downstream power stations and towns.
After the danger occurred, the local government organized the evacuation of residents along the river overnight and urgently moved the people to a safe area.
At present, 162 households and 520 people in the dangerous area have all been evacuated, and the disposal of the barrier lake is still in progress.
