Professor Huang Xiaojin, Director of Vascular Surgery, Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University, was interviewed by the media.
The Department of Vascular Surgery, Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University, is the first independent vascular surgery in Fujian Province. It has long been committed to the diagnosis and treatment of aortic and peripheral vascular diseases. In 2018, it was approved to build a provincial key clinical specialty.
In the treatment of aortic diseases, in addition to the treatment of dissecting aneurysms and aortic aneurysms, he has rich experience in emergency ruptured aortic aneurysms.
“The Department of Vascular Surgery, Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University, is outstanding in this region from the history of development, the breadth, difficulty, and complexity of the operation. Therefore, we established a collaboration center this time. In addition to the aorta, we can also In the diagnosis and treatment of lower extremity arteries, carotid arteries and other diseases, we will carry out in-depth cooperation in all aspects of medicine, teaching, and scientific research.”
Said Professor Feng Rui, deputy director of the Department of Vascular Surgery of Shanghai Changhai Hospital.
Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University and Shanghai Changhai Hospital signed a contract in 2018 to establish the “Li Zhaoshen Famous Doctor Studio” in the Department of Gastroenterology.
