The reporter learned at the meeting that vascular disease is the leading cause of death in China. The aorta, as the main artery of various organs in the human body, flows from the heart to the whole body and plays an important role.
The occurrence of aortic disease is often accompanied by high risk, high mortality, and high difficulty in treatment. The thickest section of the aorta is 4 cm in diameter. Once a hemangioma is formed, rupture occurs, or the vascular intima ruptures to produce dissection, it will cause Hemorrhage is very dangerous.
In recent years, as people’s lifestyles have changed and the pace of life has accelerated, China has become the world’s largest country with hypertension, and aortic diseases have also increased. Nowadays, with the development of surgical techniques and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases Continue to develop towards a minimally invasive, fast and efficient direction.
Doctors can puncture the thigh and place a stent in the aorta to properly “divert” the blood flow, thereby avoiding the impact on aneurysm or ruptured dissection and achieving good therapeutic results. Some operations even require local anesthesia.
This academic seminar invited more than ten domestic experts to discuss the new progress in the treatment of aortic diseases, and carried out cutting-edge technical training and difficult case discussions in the form of a conference salon.
The reporter learned at the meeting that with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the current treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in a minimally invasive, fast and efficient direction.
