The longest high-speed rail tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir area runs through - chinanews.com
2020-07-26 17:34:48 Source: China News Net Author: Chen Haifeng Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Small Three Gorges Tunnel.
Photo courtesy of China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Company
chinanews.com, Chongqing, July 26 (Reporter Han Lu) The reporter learned from the China Railway Chengdu Group Co., Ltd. on the 26th that the Zhengzhou-Wanzhou High-speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers was completed on the same day.
It is understood that the Small Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed rail tunnel within the Three Gorges Reservoir area, but also the longest single-hole double-track high-speed rail tunnel with a design speed of 350 km/h among the projects currently under construction in China.
Zhengzhou-Wanzhou High-speed Railway is located in Henan, Hubei, and Chongqing. It connects with Beijing-Guangzhou and Xuzhou-Lanzhou High-speed Railways in the north of Zhengzhou, and connects the Yuzhou-Wanzhou High-speed Railways to Chongqing in the south of Wanzhou. An important part of the Hunan Passage.
The Zhengzhou-Wanzhou High-speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel was fully completed on the 26th.
The picture shows through the scene.
The Zhengzhou-Wanzhou High-speed Railway starts in Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and runs southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, and Xiangyang City in Hubei Province to Wanzhou District of Chongqing City. The new line is about 818 kilometers in length, with a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, and about 184 kilometers in Chongqing.
Among them, the Zhengzhou-Xiangyang section has been opened for operation in advance on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up its construction.
The Small Three Gorges Tunnel, which passed through on the 26th, is a full-line control project of Zhengzhou-Wanzhou High-speed Railway. The project is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County in Chongqing City. It has a total length of about 18.9 kilometers and a maximum buried depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel started in February 2017, and the tunnel will be completed on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Guojun, head of Zhengzhou-Wanzhou High-speed Railway tunnel design of China Railway Second Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the survey and design party, the site of the Small Three Gorges Tunnel is very complex and faces risks such as karst, mud and water inrush, and large deformation of soft rock. For Class I high-risk tunnels, tunnel design and construction are extremely difficult.
“During the construction of the project, we used geological survey methods, geophysical methods and advanced drilling methods to make advance geological forecasts, and adopted special design plans for more than 30 caves of various types. For example, we designed and built a 24-meter-long bridge that spans the tunnel. Large karst caves with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters can avoid tunnel settlement.” Wang Guojun said.
According to the construction party, China Railway Tunnel Bureau, the construction of the tunnel adopted a combination of dredging and blocking, through the construction of horizontal tunnels, grouting, water blocking, strengthening of the tunnel structure support, and construction of sewage treatment stations, which ensured the orderly progress of the project. It also avoids the damage of construction drainage to the water body of the Small Three Gorges Scenic Area. At the same time, it successfully overcomes the construction problems of 7 kilometers long soft rock large deformation and other bad geology, and daily maximum water inflow of 157,000 cubic meters. .
After the Zhengzhou-Wanzhou High-speed Railway is completed and opened to traffic, it will become a new convenient and fast passenger passage from Southwest China to the Central Plains, North China, and Northeast China. It will help improve the capacity and quality of the northeast railway passage in the Southwest, improve the regional road network layout, and speed up tourism along the route. The process of resource development and urbanization is of great significance to promote coordinated regional development and to promote the implementation of the strategy for the development of the western region.
