chinanews.com, July 26. According to the Supreme Procuratorate website, in the first half of this year, prosecutors nationwide prosecuted 58,101 people for fraud, a year-on-year increase of 35%.
Especially in crimes that hinder the prevention and control of the epidemic, fraud crimes occur frequently, and the number of people prosecuted by the prosecutors for fraud accounted for 43.4% of all crimes that hinder the prevention and control of the epidemic.
The Supreme People’s Procuratorate has carried out targeted guidance. Among the ten batches of typical cases involving epidemic prevention and control that have been released so far, there are 9 cases involving fraud.
Judging from the case handling by the procuratorial organs in the first half of the year, there are many names involved in fraud crimes, ranging from national macro policies to people’s clothing, food, housing and transportation, including epidemic-related fraud, “medical care” fraud, “health care product” fraud, “admission agency” fraud, The “routine loan” fraud, the fraud of obtaining state subsidies, the fraud of national assets unfreezing, etc., continue to “innovate”, covering education, medical care, employment, pension, social security, land acquisition and demolition, targeted poverty alleviation, financial credit and other fields. The victims caused economic losses and also seriously affected economic and social development.
In particular, some telecommunications network frauds break through the restrictions of national boundaries, regions and personnel, and have the characteristics of stakeholder, cross-border, remote, electronic payment, etc., and there are many unspecified victim groups and great harm.
For example, some set up specialized companies, rent high-end office buildings, set up multiple departments or positions, use legal network platforms to promote and recruit, train and assess recruiters, adopt corporate operation mode management, and wear “legal cloak” to confuse Stronger sex.
Punishing and preventing crimes in accordance with the law, and promptly issuing early warnings to the public and relevant departments are the inescapable responsibilities of procuratorial organs.
In handling judicial cases, procuratorial organs conscientiously perform their duties, not only insisting on maintaining a high-pressure posture against fraud crimes, but also targeting specific law enforcement measures, and promoting social governance by issuing procuratorial recommendations.
The procuratorial organs strictly control the facts, evidence, procedures, and application of law in approving and prosecuting fraud cases, based on facts, and the law as the criterion, so as to be indulgent.
Especially for telecommunication network fraud crimes, we pay attention to the core role of electronic data in fact determination, and strive to build an evidence chain that mutually confirms electronic data, verbal evidence, and documentary evidence.
For example, the Yinzhou District Procuratorate of Ningbo City, Zhejiang Province handled a certain epidemic-related fraud case, and the prosecutors intervened as soon as possible. From the occurrence of the case to the completion of the case, it only took 5 days, which reflects that it is handled quickly and strictly, and the overall stability of the society is maintained. Attitude and determination.
In the process of reviewing arrests and reviewing prosecutions, we focused on the prosecution of missed offenders, corrected 733 people who were missed by the public security organs, and corrected the public security organs’ omission to review and prosecute 1113 accomplices.
In the first half of the year, procuratorial organs across the country issued 298 procuratorial recommendations for fraud crimes, promoting joint efforts to prevent fraud crimes and promoting in-depth governance.
For example, in response to the loopholes in the supervision of telecommunications companies, banks, and intermediary organizations found in the handling of the case, the Guangzhou Procuratorate of Guangdong Province and the Dongguan Procuratorate promptly put forward procuratorial recommendations, urging relevant units to strengthen supervision, improve mechanisms, and promote the leaders Effective system construction.
The fourth is to do a good job in recovering stolen goods and saving damage.
